  <metadata>
    <name>Lingmoor Fell and Langdale from Elterwater</name>
    <bounds minlat="54.4250404" minlon="-3.1005887" maxlat="54.4461416" maxlon="-3.0382579" />
  </metadata>
  <rte>
    <name>Lingmoor Fell and Langdale from Elterwater</name>
    <desc>At 1,530 feet, Lingmoor Fell is less than half the height of Scafell Pike, England's highest mountain just a few miles away. As so often happens with an isolated peak, the quality of the views more than makes up for any lack of altitude.</desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1684-description</url>
